All roads in Johannesburg lead to Orlando Stadium where the official memorial for Winnie Madikizela-Mandela will take place on Wednesday morning.
The SA Police Service has warned that roads leading to the stadium will be closed to traffic. A shuttle service will be provided from the Nasrec train station.
The anti-apartheid struggle stalwart and former wife of Nelson Mandela died at the age of 81 on Easter Monday.
Developing story.
– African News Agency (ANA)


